 "components": {
  "instruction": "Classify the given text into one of these categories: abbreviation, description, entity, human, location, numeric.\n\nUse the following definitions to guide your classification:\n- abbreviation: Questions asking what an abbreviation or acronym stands for\n- description: Questions asking for a definition, explanation, or description of something\n- entity: Questions asking about things, objects, organizations, concepts, or possessions (e.g., \"What instrument did X play?\", \"What company does X own?\")\n- human: Questions asking for the identity of a person or people (e.g., \"Who invented X?\", \"Who is the CEO of X?\")\n- location: Questions asking for a place, country, city, or geographical location\n- numeric: Questions asking for numerical values, dates, quantities, or amounts\n\nImportant distinctions:\n- When a question asks \"What [thing] did [person] [verb]?\" (e.g., \"What musical instrument did Sherlock Holmes play?\"), classify it as 'entity' because it's asking about a thing or object, not about a person's identity.\n- Only classify as 'human' when the question is asking for the identity or name of a person, not when a person is merely mentioned in the question."
